# 🎯 Root Cause

👉 MachineConfig NOT applied properly on **ocp-cp-3**

So:

* cp-1, cp-2 → using new mirror ✔
* cp-3 → still using old mirror ❌

👉 Your failing pods are scheduled on cp-3 → failure

---

# 🚀 FINAL FIX (target only cp-3)

## ✅ Step 1: Force MachineConfig re-apply on cp-3

Run:

```bash
oc debug node/ocp-cp-3
chroot /host
systemctl restart machine-config-daemon
```

---

## ✅ Step 2: Restart CRI-O

```bash
systemctl restart crio
exit
```

---

## ✅ Step 3: Verify config is fixed

```bash
oc debug node/ocp-cp-3
chroot /host
cat /etc/containers/registries.conf
```

👉 It MUST match cp-1 / cp-2:

```text
bastion...:8443/openshift4   ✅
```

👉 And NOT:

```text
ocp4/openshift4 ❌
```

---

## 🔥 If still not fixed (strong fix)

Force re-sync from MCO:

```bash
oc delete pod -n openshift-machine-config-operator -l k8s-app=machine-config-daemon
```

👉 This will recreate daemon and fix node

---

## ✅ Step 4: Delete failing pods

```bash
oc get pods -A | grep -i pull | awk '{print $1, $2}' | while read ns pod; do
  oc delete pod $pod -n $ns
done
```

